Document: DampedSpringJoint2D  
Path: godot/classes/class_dampedspringjoint2d.rst  
Summary: Properties controlling damping, length, rest length, and stiffness of a 2D damped spring joint.  

damping (float): Spring joint's damping ratio. A value between 0 and 1. When bodies move in different directions, the system aligns them to the spring axis. High damping forces faster alignment. Default: 1.0. Methods: set_damping(float) → void, get_damping() → float.  

length (float): Maximum allowed length of the spring joint. Bodies cannot stretch it beyond this value. Default: 50.0. Methods: set_length(float) → void, get_length() → float.  

rest_length (float): Target length the joint tries to resize toward when bodies move. Default: 0.0. Methods: set_rest_length(float) → void, get_rest_length() → float.  

stiffness (float): Determines how much the joint resists deformation. Higher values reduce deformation. Force applied is stiffness multiplied by the difference from rest length. Default: 20.0. Methods: set_stiffness(float) → void, get_stiffness() → float.